data.name: label1.Text
data.value: LedControl.ini files are used by the DirectOutput framework as a fallback solution if no cable config can be found or if the table config contains errors. If no LedControl.ini files are specified in this table, the framework will try to lookup a file called ledcontrol.ini in the following locations: - Table directory - Global config directory - Directory of the framework The LedControl.ini file(s) will be used to control LedWizEquivalent toys (basically a pass through to a Ledwiz output controller). The cabinet config can contain any number of LedwizEquivalent toys, each having a identifiaction number between 0-15 which is the equivalent to the number of a ledwiz. The first LedControl.ini file, will control LedwizEquivalent nr. 1, the second file will control nr. 2 and so on. If the cabinet config does not contain LedWizEquivalent toys and no LedWiz output controllers or if no cabinet config is available, the framework will try to locate all connected Ledwiz controllers and add the necessary objects (LedWiz output controllers and LedWizEquivalent toys) to the config. Check the Docu on the DirectOutput framework for more information.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
The table config file pattern specifies the the name for the table config file. The usual wildcards for filenames are supported for this setting: - * is the wildcard for any number of characters - ? is the wildcard for a single character In addition to the wildcards the framework does also support the following placeholders: - {GlobalConfigDir} path to the global config cirectory - {DllDir} path to the directory of the DirectOutput.dll - {TableDir} path to the table directory - {TableDirName} name of the table directory (last part of the path) - {TableName} name of the table without extension.
Please check the docu on the DirectOutput framework for more information.
